↑ Elevating"},{"url":"https://www.htnxt.com/page/How-to-Select-a-Smart-PDU-Supplier-for-Data-Centers:-A-Technical-Buyers-Guide-(2026).html","stance":"silent","quote":"Procurement professionals must evaluate vendors not only on technical specifications but also on real-world deployment track records, certifications, and support capabilities."},{"url":"https://www.idcpdu.com/news/industry-news/pdu-lead-time-and-production-factors-in-custom-orders.html","stance":"silent","quote":"Custom PDU orders often take longer than buyers expect because lead time depends on far more than basic electrical ratings."}],"status":"corroborated","statusRationale":"The load-bearing premise — that new-build DC electrical BOMs are locked at design freeze well ahead of energization due to long-lead power gear — is directly and strongly corroborated by multiple independent industry sources. Build.inc explicitly states procurement must precede design and transformers run 48-60 months; Construction Business Outlook confirms gear must be released before topology is finalized; VAWN's lead-time index shows 128-week transformers. However, the specific sub-claim that PDUs specifically ride along with the electrical BOM (rather than being procured late as a commodity line) is not directly evidenced. PDU sourcing guides describe RFQ/competitive selection processes but say nothing about their timing relative to design freeze — leaving the PDU-specific coupling inferential. The falsifier (late competitive PDU selection) is neither confirmed nor refuted by the retrieved PDU material.","evidence":[{"title":"Data Center Electrical Procurement: Why the Order Has to Come Before the Design","sourceType":"industry-report","publisher":"Build.inc","date":"2026-06-22","excerpt":"Power transformer lead times from major manufacturers have reached 48 to 60 months. Generator step-up transformers average 144 weeks. Tier 1 suppliers -- ABB, Siemens Energy, Hitachi Energy -- have backlogs extending to 2030 and beyond. A developer who sequences procurement conventionally and targets energization in 2028 has already missed the window.","url":"https://build.inc/insights/data-center-electrical-procurement-sequence-workflow"},{"title":"From Electrical Design to Energization","sourceType":"industry-report","publisher":"Construction Business Outlook","date":"2026-04-20","excerpt":"the schedule can be effectively lost before a single foundation is poured...because a transformer with a 65-week lead time wasn't released before the topology was finalized. Contractors who consistently deliver these programs on time have stopped treating electrical planning as a downstream task.","url":"https://constructionbusinessoutlook.com/from-electrical-design-to-energization/"},{"title":"Electrical Equipment Lead Time Index","sourceType":"industry-report","publisher":"VAWN","date":"2026-06-02","excerpt":"Power / substation transformer 128 weeks ↑ Elevating; Generator step-up (GSU) transformer 144 weeks ↑ Elevating; Medium-voltage switchgear 44 weeks. Panelboards 15-23 weeks; Circuit breakers (commodity) In stock.","url":"https://usevawn.com/resources/electrical-equipment-lead-times/"}],"revisedLikelihood":0.55,"revisionRationale":"The core premise of early electrical lock-in for new builds is now strongly corroborated by multiple independent sources (exceeding the 12-24mo window the ledger uses), which modestly strengthens the hypothesis. However, the crucial unquantified gap remains: no retrieved evidence establishes whether rack PDUs specifically ride the frozen BOM or are procured late as a commodity line — the PDU sourcing guides describe RFQ processes without timing relative to design freeze. This keeps the likelihood near coin-flip; the trigger is well-supported but the PDU-coupling link that makes it consequential is still inferential."}
